<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN">
<html>
<head>
<title>Help: Setting up manager notification options</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<link href="../style.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
</head>

<body>
<p class="titlebold">Setting up manager notification options</p>
<p class="text">To change the notification options, go to Browse under Users
  in the main VariaPrint&#8482; manager menu and select the &quot;Manager accounts&quot; submenu.
  Select &quot;Notification options...&quot; for your account and &quot;Access
  / Notification options ...&quot; for other managers to change the notification
options. See also <a href="users-approval.php" target="mainFrame">Setting
up approval managers</a>.</p>
<p class="text">Managers can be notified by email for a couple different events:</p>
<p class="text"><strong>PO account approval</strong><br>
  If the order site accepts PO accounts,  when a request is made to set up
    a PO account any given number of managers can be notified that a request
    has been made. Generally, only one manager would need to be notified. </p>
<p class="text"><strong>Process a  new order</strong><br>
   Make sure the manager's access/notification options has the &quot;Notify on new
     order&quot; and &quot;Download impositions&quot; checked.</p>
<p class="text"><strong>Approving a new order</strong><br> 
  See <a href="users-approval.php" target="mainFrame">Setting up approval managers</a>.
</p>
</body>
</html>
